article.headline: Tulsa 74, TCU 62
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Anthony Price scored 19 points on 9-of-11 shooting from the field and grabbed nine rebounds as Tulsa beat TCU 74-62 on Saturday night. Tulsa (2-1) also got 17 points from Jason Parker and Kenneth Kelley. Jarius Glenn added 10 points and eight boards for Tulsa. Price also had three steals and three blocks. TCU (1-1) struggled from the field, shooting 31 percent in the first half and trailing 41-30 at halftime. Tulsa shot 51 percent for the game and never trailed. Corey Santee led TCU with 15 points and Chudi Chinweze added 13.
